{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567212","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567212"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:57:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:57:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18948"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18948","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18948"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.82,0.01,0.07,0.09,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11682"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106298"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11682","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11682"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18948"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88766"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1604"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5644"},{"type":"tags","id":"5770"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11298"},{"type":"tags","id":"11352"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27486"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27494"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37351"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106298","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/106298"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor posts on their public social media account about attending a party where they became heavily intoxicated. The post includes photos of them engaging in inappropriate behaviour while wearing clothing that identifies them as medical staff from their hospital.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes why this behaviour is concerning from a professional standpoint?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["It undermines public trust in the medical profession","It undermines how colleagues view the offending doctor","It promotes disrespect of hospital property","It promotes unhealthy behaviour","It demonstrates poor work-life balance"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe key issue is that this behaviour \u003Cstrong\u003Eundermines public trust in the medical profession\u003C/strong\u003E. Medical professionals hold a privileged position of public trust that extends beyond working hours. Actions that diminish this trust can damage both individual and collective professional standing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt undermines how colleagues view the offending doctor\u003C/strong\u003E - The main issue is not colleague perception but rather public trust and professional standing\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt promotes disrespect of hospital property\u003C/strong\u003E - While wearing hospital clothing inappropriately is unprofessional, the main concern is the broader impact on public trust\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt promotes unhealthy behaviour\u003C/strong\u003E - While the behaviour may be unhealthy, the professional concern is primarily about maintaining public trust\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt demonstrates poor work-life balance\u003C/strong\u003E - The concern is not about balance but about maintaining professional standards in public contexts\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMedical professionals must recognise that their behaviour, even outside of work hours, can impact their professional standing and the reputation of the medical profession as a whole. This includes being mindful of how personal activities might be perceived when shared on social media platforms. In addition to this, public behaviour in professional attire (clothing provided by the hospital and identifying the individual as being a member of the medical staff force) provides a direct link to the institution which compounds the potential for reputational harm and damage to public trust.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Medical professionals have ethical obligations that extend beyond work hours due to their position of public trust.","Social media posts can impact professional reputation and patient confidence even when made outside of work.","Professional behaviour guidelines apply to both work and personal contexts for healthcare workers."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","Medical Board of Australia. Social media: How to meet your obligations under the National Law [internet]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available from: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/Codes-Guidelines-Policies/Social-media-guidance.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88766"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18948"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88766","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88766"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-17T18:59:28+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-17T19:01:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11682"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106298"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":